parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause extended stopping distances, loss of brake effectiveness, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal travels to the floor

with no braking at the other three wheels; the ABS warning light comes on; the vehicle takes longer to stop than expected; the brake pedal becomes hard or stiff; the vehicle slows down but does not stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the brake pedal can cause the brakes to fail, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes to the floor; the brake pedal feels soft or spongy; the brake pedal does not return to its normal position; the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position; the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake hydraulic system can cause the brakes to fail, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy; the brake pedal goes to the floor; the brake pedal does not return to its normal position; the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position; the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel system failures can cause fuel leaks, engine stalling, and difficulty starting the vehicle, which can lead to accidents, fires, or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Fuel smell inside or around the vehicle
faulty rubber air intake conductor getting hot.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause a fire, leading to a risk of injury or death, and can also cause the vehicle to become inoperable, leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Smoke pouring out of the hood
